model_explanation: S1 says the only thing Sam gave Tom was apples, but S2 says Sam gave Tom something else—grapes—which contradicts that.
S1 talks specifically about Mary and what Sam gave her, while S2 discusses Bill without directly relating to the claim about Mary. They are independent.
S1 says Mary only got apples, but S2 says she also got bananas, directly contradicting the assertion in S1.
S1 is about what Sue received from Sam, while S2 is about what Rob did not receive. There’s no direct connection, so they are independent.
S1 says that Bill only got bananas, but S2 says Bill got grapes as well, which contradicts the exclusivity implied by “only” in S1.
if Rob only got grapes from Sam, then it logically follows that Rob didn’t get apples from him.
S1 is about what Sue received and S2 is about what Tom received. There’s no direct contradiction or entailment. They’re unrelated.
if Ellen is the only one receiving grapes, then Rob didn’t receive them. So S2 is entailed by S1.
if Mary only got grapes, then she didn’t get bananas. But S2 says she did, which contradicts S1.
if Sue is the only person who got apples, that means Bill didn’t get any apples. So S2 is entailed by S1.
